4. Privacy & sanitisation rules (THE most important section)
The reporter must never see the diagnostics blob. The diagnostics blob must never contain
secrets or third-party PII beyond what's needed to debug. Enforce in this order:

Two-tier payload. The popup builds two objects: userVisible (title, description, category,
screenshot) and diagnostics (everything else). The diagnostics object is assembled client-side
but scrubbed both client- and server-side before persistence (defence in depth).

Allowlist, not denylist, for session/flags. Only copy known-safe fields: roles, dbUserId,
authStatus, isDevLogin. Never copy NextAuth tokens, JWTs, cookies, NEXTAUTH_SECRET,
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY, or any process.env value that isn't NEXT_PUBLIC_* and on an explicit allowlist.

Redaction pass (reuse the redaction approach already in src/lib/audit/auditLog.js). Run a
regex/key scrubber over all strings in console_errors, failed_requests.url, recent_actions,
and stack traces to strip: bearer/JWT tokens (/eyJ[\w-]+\.[\w-]+\.[\w-]+/), API keys
(sk_, service_role, long hex/base64 blobs), emails (mask to a***@domain), NI numbers,
card-number patterns, query-string ?token=/?key=/?secret= values, and Authorization headers.

Request bodies are NOT captured — only method, URL (path, query stripped of secret keys),
status code, and duration. Never log request/response bodies.

Screenshot is user-initiated only. No automatic/silent screen capture. The user must click
"Attach screenshot" and the image is captured client-side (see §6). Show the user a preview so
they can see exactly what is being sent and redact (draw black boxes) before submitting.

Server-side re-scrub on ingest. The API route runs the same sanitiser again on diagnostics
before insert — the client is untrusted. Reject payloads over a size cap (e.g. 256 KB JSON).

Storage isolation. Screenshots go to a private bucket (support-reports), never public.
Signed URLs (short TTL) generated server-side only for admin viewer.

Retention. Add support_reports to the existing retention runner (tools/scripts/run-retention.js)
— e.g. purge resolved/wont_fix reports + screenshots after N days. Document the window.

RLS. Enable Row Level Security on support_reports: a reporter may INSERT and SELECT only
their own rows' user-visible columns (via a view); the diagnostics column is only readable by
the service-role / admin API. Simplest safe approach: never expose the table to the anon client at
all — all reads/writes go through role-guarded API routes using supabaseService.

5. UI / UX flow
All UI must comply with CLAUDE.md §3 (LayerSurface/LayerTheme alternation, no borders on
surfaces, tokens only, responsive, 44px touch targets). Reuse PopupModal, model the form on
NextActionPrompt, acknowledge via AlertContext.

The "?" control — a text/icon button ("?") in the topbar right column of
StaffTopbar.js, placed between GlobalSearch and NextActionPrompt. It is purely
presentational; it calls a callback passed down from StaffLayout, or (preferred) consumes a
new lightweight SupportReportContext mounted in _app.js so any component can call
openSupportReport({ prefill }). Always visible to all authenticated users.

Open → popup (SupportReportModal, new, under src/components/support/):

Step 1: short friendly intro + a category chooser (bug / question / visual / data / other).

Step 2: title (optional) + description (required, the "describe what happened" box).

Step 3: Attach screenshot (optional but encouraged): "Capture this screen" button →
client-side capture (see §6) → preview with simple redaction (draw rectangles) → confirm.

A subtle, collapsed "What we'll send to the developers" disclosure that lists the categories
of diagnostic data (route, device, recent errors) in plain language — for transparency/GDPR — but
not the raw values. (Privacy-by-design + user trust.)

Submit button (primary). Esc/backdrop closes (inherited from PopupModal).

On submit: show optimistic "Sending…", then a success toast via AlertContext
("Thanks — your report #1234 was sent to the team"). On failure, keep the popup open with the
